member.summary:
The PDMFieldIterator is used to iterate through each {@link PDMField}
           in a {@link PDMMessage}.  Check isValueSet() before accessing its value
           to determine if the {@link PDMField} has been set.

The PDMOffsetTable is used internally by a {@link PDMMessage}
           when optional or variable fields are set and then is
           written on the wire as field id and offset into the data segment.
